  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Light &amp; Life for Persons with Intellectual and Developmental Disabilities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hogares Luteranos el Buen Pastor (HLBP) serves people with intellectual and developmental disabilities. This project will provide a renewable energy source that will supply reliable electricity to HLBP&#x2019;s group home ~ &quot;Casa Hogar&quot; and Concordia Lutheran School &amp;amp; Mercy Center as well as strengthen the viability of a farm on their campus in Palmar Arriba. The project supports the on-going care of orphaned adolescents and young adults with IDD in &#x201C;Casa Hogar&#x201D; - an exemplary alternative to institutionalization; a new vocational pilot program to provide opportunities for persons with IDD to receive training and access to meaningful employment; additional training and advocacy in the IDD ward of the state psychiatric hospital; and provision of consistent electricity, water and ultimately food sources to the Casa Hogar and surrounding Palmar Arriba community.</narrative>
  </description>
